What it is?
SonarQube is a Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tool.

What it does?
Scans source code without running it
Finds:
    Bugs
    Security vulnerabilities
    Code smells
    Duplicate code

Key features:
    Quality Gates (fail build if issues found)
    Supports multiple languages (Java, Python, JS, etc.)
    Integrates with:
          Azure DevOps
          Jenkins
          GitHub Actions

Example:
      Detects:
          SQL Injection risks
          Hardcoded passwords
          Poor coding practices
